# Active Global Tasks

## Governance
- Finalize multichain governance architecture — 80%
- Isolate Harmony-specific logic — 78%
- Implement chain registry — 84%
- Expose governance plugin capabilities and indexing readiness through the backend chain registry — 82%
- Implement federation records — 46%; in progress: chain registry now exposes federation membership, tier, roles, local autonomy boundary, federation requirements and initial DAO tenant account context through the Constitutional Layer
- Implement DAO tenant account layer — 46%; in progress: backend exposes `/v2/governance/tenants`, derives tenant accounts from indexed DAO registry records when available, preserves bootstrap fallback tenants, and AxodusAPP renders the selected DAO as an operational tenant account with treasury, members/roles, products, agents, proposals, operations, receipts and reason codes
- Implement proposal aggregation flows — 38%
- Implement backend createProposal contract — 81%; in progress: `/v2/proposals/create` accepts enriched non-on-chain review submissions from AxodusAPP, `GET /v2/proposals/create/:id` reads observed receipts, `GET /v2/proposals/create` lists selected-context review receipts, persisted and memory fallback receipts expose `storageMode`, `source`, and indexer reconciliation metadata, persistence was validated through `CreateProposalRequest` with Mongo connected, explicit in-memory fallback remains for bootstrap/offline API mode, and `service-aragon-api` compose accepts external `MONGO_DB_URI` injection without hardcoding secrets
- Implement constitutional execution conditions — 38%; in progress: registry exposes normalized Constitutional Layer conditions for chain enablement, execution authorization, plugin capability registration, local standing, treasury review, and agent permission scope
- Implement Constitutional Guardrails with transparent reason codes — 80%; in progress: registry, indexer readiness, backend createProposal boundaries, frontend governance guards, createProposal storage fallback, observed registry/DAO/plugin/treasury policy sources, and Constitutional Layer execution models expose reason codes
- Model Constitutional Governance and Local Governance as distinct governance nuclei — 86%; in progress: chain/plugin capabilities now expose constitutional and local governance context plus authority, federation, and execution boundaries

